Fix the github-relay deployment to properly support Tailscale Funnel instead of using a tsnsrv stub.

## Problem
The current PR adds a stub for services.tsnsrv because classic-laddie doesn't have the tsnsrv module. But we actually want Funnel enabled so GitHub can reach the relay publicly.

## Changes needed

### 1. Add tsnsrv flake input (flake.nix)
tsnsrv is at github:boinkor-net/tsnsrv. Add it as a flake input:
```nix
tsnsrv = {
  url = "github:boinkor-net/tsnsrv";
  inputs.nixpkgs.follows = "nixpkgs";
};
```

Also add tsnsrv to the outputs function parameters.

### 2. Import the tsnsrv NixOS module
In the classic-laddie nixosSystem modules list, add:
```nix
tsnsrv.nixosModules.default
```

### 3. Remove the stub module
Delete the entire stub block that was added:
```nix
# Stub: github-relay module references services.tsnsrv for funnel
# support; declare the option so evaluation succeeds even without
# the tsnsrv module imported (funnel is not enabled).
(
  { lib, ... }:
  {
    options.services.tsnsrv = lib.mkOption {
      ...
    };
  }
)
```

### 4. Enable funnel on the github-relay config
In hosts/classic-laddie/default.nix, add funnel.enable to the github-relay config:
```nix
services.github-relay = {
  enable = true;
  port = 8077;
  webhookSecretFile = config.age.secrets.github-webhook-secret.path;
  funnel.enable = true;  # ADD THIS
  consumers = { ... };
};
```

### 5. Ensure Tailscale is configured
Check if services.tailscale is already enabled on classic-laddie. If not, it needs to be for Funnel to work. Look at the existing config.

### 6. Update flake.lock
Run: nix flake update tsnsrv

### 7. Verify
Run: nix flake check or nix build .#nixosConfigurations.classic-laddie.config.system.build.toplevel --dry-run
